[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi Everybody,<br>\nI'm developing the NBG set theory in Lean, just for fun. Any suggestions?</p>",
        "id": 194652217,
        "sender_full_name": "aes_triplex",
        "timestamp": 1587375426
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>take the model of ZFC and translate it to NBG</p>",
        "id": 194655811,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1587377764
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>because lean has higher order quantifiers, the model of ZFC is also a model of NBG, even MK set theory</p>",
        "id": 194655914,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1587377835
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>to be clear, I'm talking about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/set_theory/zfc.html#Set\" title=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/set_theory/zfc.html#Set\">https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/set_theory/zfc.html#Set</a></p>",
        "id": 194656518,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1587378167
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110049\">@Mario Carneiro</span> is there an interface <code>structure model_of_ZFC</code> which <code>Set</code> is an instance of?</p>",
        "id": 194656550,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1587378187
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>no</p>",
        "id": 194656652,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1587378243
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>actually Jesse and Floris probably built such a thing</p>",
        "id": 194656679,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1587378264
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but in <code>set_theory.zfc</code> it's just a bunch of theorems that look like the axioms of ZFC</p>",
        "id": 194656705,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1587378282
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"110049\">@Mario Carneiro</span>  thanks.<br>\nIs there any feature (regarding set theory or axiomatic theories) on which I could eventually work?</p>",
        "id": 194665930,
        "sender_full_name": "aes_triplex",
        "timestamp": 1587384839
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>generally speaking, it is easier to work with models than with axiomatic theories described via a deeply embedded formal language</p>",
        "id": 194666044,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1587384912
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But if you want to go the FOL route, you should check out <a href=\"https://github.com/flypitch/flypitch/\" title=\"https://github.com/flypitch/flypitch/\">https://github.com/flypitch/flypitch/</a></p>",
        "id": 194666096,
        "sender_full_name": "Mario Carneiro",
        "timestamp": 1587384953
    }
]